{"title":"Holiday Gift Guide – What to get your favorite cyclist!","link":"https://bikerumor.com/2021/10/31/cycling-holiday-gift-guide/","date":1635714039000,"content":"<div id=\"readability-page-1\" class=\"page\"><div><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/28132856/Cyclist-Gift-Guide-Feature-final.jpg\" data-fancybox=\"\"><img width=\"800\" height=\"534\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/28132856/Cyclist-Gift-Guide-Feature-final-800x534.jpg\" alt=\"holiday gift guide shows the best gifts for cyclists\" loading=\"lazy\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/28132856/Cyclist-Gift-Guide-Feature-final-800x534.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/28132856/Cyclist-Gift-Guide-Feature-final-297x198.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/28132856/Cyclist-Gift-Guide-Feature-final-120x80.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/28132856/Cyclist-Gift-Guide-Feature-final-768x513.jpg 768w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/28132856/Cyclist-Gift-Guide-Feature-final-1536x1025.jpg 1536w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/28132856/Cyclist-Gift-Guide-Feature-final.jpg 1600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\"></a><header></header><p>Support us! BikeRumor may earn a small commission from affiliate links in this article. <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/privacy\" target=\"_blank\">Learn more</a>.</p></div><div role=\"main\"><article id=\"post-276128\" role=\"article\" itemscope=\"\" itemtype=\"http://schema.org/BlogPosting\"><section itemprop=\"text\"><p>This season, we’re publishing different gift guides for different types of riders, from road to gravel to MTB and more. But for those of us who ride <em>all</em> the things, or are just getting into the sport and haven’t found our tribe yet, there are basics that are loved by anyone who’s pedaling two wheels for fun or exercise.</p><p>Here are our top gift ideas for the cyclist (or cyclists!) in your circle, from budget stocking stuffers to roll-up-the-garage-door surprises at every price point…</p><h2>Best Cycling Gifts under $25</h2><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/25145119/HGG-general-25.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/25145119/HGG-general-25.jpg\" alt=\"best gifts for cyclists under 25 dollars\" width=\"1232\" height=\"762\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/25145119/HGG-general-25.jpg 1232w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/25145119/HGG-general-25-297x184.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/25145119/HGG-general-25-800x495.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/25145119/HGG-general-25-120x74.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/25145119/HGG-general-25-768x475.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1232px) 100vw, 1232px\"></a></p><p><strong>Blackburn Designs Grid Medium Seat Bag</strong> ($23, available at <a href=\"https://www.avantlink.com/click.php?tt=el&amp;merchant_id=92594cfb-2b30-40ba-ab76-f9c20ed4612c&amp;website_id=3407ca35-0b50-44fe-aeb1-9ab6a93bba54&amp;url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.competitivecyclist.com%2Fblackburn-grid-seat-bag&amp;ctc=brbgoutdoorbikinggeneralgg|xid:fr1635716343820jdc\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\" data-orig-url=\"https://www.avantlink.com/click.php?tt=el&amp;merchant_id=92594cfb-2b30-40ba-ab76-f9c20ed4612c&amp;website_id=3407ca35-0b50-44fe-aeb1-9ab6a93bba54&amp;url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.competitivecyclist.com%2Fblackburn-grid-seat-bag&amp;ctc=brbgoutdoorbikinggeneralgg\" data-ml-id=\"0\" data-ml=\"true\" data-xid=\"fr1635716343820jdc\">Competitive Cyclist</a> and <a href=\"https://www.avantlink.com/click.php?tt=el&amp;merchant_id=b5770911-39dc-46ac-ba0f-b49dbb30c5c7&amp;website_id=3407ca35-0b50-44fe-aeb1-9ab6a93bba54&amp;url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.backcountry.com%2Fblackburn-grid-seat-bag&amp;ctc=brbgoutdoorbikinggeneralgg|xid:fr1635716343820bje\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\" data-orig-url=\"https://www.avantlink.com/click.php?tt=el&amp;merchant_id=b5770911-39dc-46ac-ba0f-b49dbb30c5c7&amp;website_id=3407ca35-0b50-44fe-aeb1-9ab6a93bba54&amp;url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.backcountry.com%2Fblackburn-grid-seat-bag&amp;ctc=brbgoutdoorbikinggeneralgg\" data-ml-id=\"1\" data-ml=\"true\" data-xid=\"fr1635716343820bje\">Backcountry</a>) has been Tyler’s go-to saddle bag for years now. It’s just the right size to fit a mini-tool, tube, CO2, patch kit, and even their tiny <strong>Airstik 2Stage mini-pump</strong> ($25, available at <a href=\"https://www.amazon.com/dp/B075RLH8X4/?tag=20br-20\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\" data-orig-url=\"https://www.amazon.com/dp/B075RLH8X4/?tag=20br-20\" data-ml-id=\"2\" data-ml=\"true\" data-xid=\"fr1635716343820jdh\">Amazon</a>)…meaning you can literally pack every essential for any ride into it for a minimalist look that cinches tight so nothing rattles around inside. Considering it’s held up to years of rides on-road and gravel rides while packed full, and that the side panels are reflective, it’s an easy recommendation.</p><p>Every cyclist needs a multi-tool along for the ride, and the <strong>Park Tool IB-2</strong> ($17, available at <a href=\"https://www.avantlink.com/click.php?tt=el&amp;merchant_id=e295c418-295a-447c-b265-734e25f82503&amp;website_id=3407ca35-0b50-44fe-aeb1-9ab6a93bba54&amp;url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.rei.com%2Fproduct%2F713812%2Fpark-tool-i-beam-mini-tool&amp;ctc=brbgoutdoorbikinggeneralgg|xid:fr1635716343820ebb\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\" data-orig-url=\"https://www.avantlink.com/click.php?tt=el&amp;merchant_id=e295c418-295a-447c-b265-734e25f82503&amp;website_id=3407ca35-0b50-44fe-aeb1-9ab6a93bba54&amp;url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.rei.com%2Fproduct%2F713812%2Fpark-tool-i-beam-mini-tool&amp;ctc=brbgoutdoorbikinggeneralgg\" data-ml-id=\"3\" data-ml=\"true\" data-xid=\"fr1635716343820ebb\">REI</a> and <a href=\"https://www.avantlink.com/click.php?tt=el&amp;merchant_id=b5770911-39dc-46ac-ba0f-b49dbb30c5c7&amp;website_id=3407ca35-0b50-44fe-aeb1-9ab6a93bba54&amp;url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.backcountry.com%2Fpark-tool-i-beam-mini-hex-screwdriver-star-set-ib-2&amp;ctc=brbgoutdoorbikinggeneralgg|xid:fr1635716343820hjj\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\" data-orig-url=\"https://www.avantlink.com/click.php?tt=el&amp;merchant_id=b5770911-39dc-46ac-ba0f-b49dbb30c5c7&amp;website_id=3407ca35-0b50-44fe-aeb1-9ab6a93bba54&amp;url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.backcountry.com%2Fpark-tool-i-beam-mini-hex-screwdriver-star-set-ib-2&amp;ctc=brbgoutdoorbikinggeneralgg\" data-ml-id=\"4\" data-ml=\"true\" data-xid=\"fr1635716343820hjj\">Backcountry</a>) has <em>most</em> of what you’ll need in a tiny, lightweight package that fits in a saddlebag, jersey pocket, or even the tiny side pockets on some hydration pack waistbands. It’s a great starter tool or a perfect replacement for the weight-weenie. (<em>Check out all <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/2021/06/25/best-bike-multitools-minitools/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">our favorite mini-tools here</a></em>)</p><p>Chamois Butt’r may be the original anti-chafe cream (or at least the best known), but it wasn’t until they introduced their <strong>Coconut Oil &amp; Shea Butter formula</strong> ($18, available at <a href=\"https://www.amazon.com/dp/B07M59S1WZ/?tag=20br-20\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\" data-orig-url=\"https://www.amazon.com/dp/B07M59S1WZ/?tag=20br-20\" data-ml-id=\"5\" data-ml=\"true\" data-xid=\"fr1635716343820efi\">Amazon</a> and <a href=\"https://www.avantlink.com/click.php?tt=el&amp;merchant_id=dbc1b0c8-d7e0-456d-84ec-281d3a696709&amp;website_id=3407ca35-0b50-44fe-aeb1-9ab6a93bba54&amp;url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.performancebike.com%2Fchamois-buttr-coconut-antichafe-cream-tube-8oz-cb-8ozccb%2Fp-fqhvsdg42eawtqhe%3Fv%3D862900&amp;ctc=brbgoutdoorbikinggeneralgg|xid:fr1635716343820fgf\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\" data-orig-url=\"https://www.avantlink.com/click.php?tt=el&amp;merchant_id=dbc1b0c8-d7e0-456d-84ec-281d3a696709&amp;website_id=3407ca35-0b50-44fe-aeb1-9ab6a93bba54&amp;url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.performancebike.com%2Fchamois-buttr-coconut-antichafe-cream-tube-8oz-cb-8ozccb%2Fp-fqhvsdg42eawtqhe%3Fv%3D862900&amp;ctc=brbgoutdoorbikinggeneralgg\" data-ml-id=\"6\" data-ml=\"true\" data-xid=\"fr1635716343820fgf\">Performance Bike</a>) that it became one of our favorites. Along with a good pair of padded shorts, a good chamois cream will improve rider comfort, especially if you’re not used to spending much time on a saddle. (<em>Check out all <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/2021/09/16/best-chamois-cream/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">our favorite chamois creams here</a></em>)</p><h2>Best Cycling Gifts under $50</h2><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/25164959/HGG-general-50.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/25164959/HGG-general-50.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1777\" height=\"583\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/25164959/HGG-general-50.jpg 1777w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/25164959/HGG-general-50-297x97.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/25164959/HGG-general-50-800x262.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/25164959/HGG-general-50-120x39.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/25164959/HGG-general-50-768x252.jpg 768w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/25164959/HGG-general-50-1536x504.jpg 1536w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1777px) 100vw, 1777px\"></a></p><p>The <strong>Topeak SmartGauge D2</strong> ($27, available at <a href=\"https://www.amazon.com/dp/B0051LQ0X4/?tag=20br-20\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\" data-orig-url=\"https://www.amazon.com/dp/B0051LQ0X4/?tag=20br-20\" data-ml-id=\"7\" data-ml=\"true\" data-xid=\"fr1635716343820gcb\">Amazon</a>) digital tire pressure gauge does a bit more than just check the air in your bike tires, it’ll also check your suspension fork and shock (up to 250psi at least, so heavier riders might find it doesn’t quite go high enough on some rear shocks). It works with both Presta and Schrader valves, rotates to keep the screen in view, and has a pressure release valve to help you dial in your setup.</p><p>The <strong>Rider Box </strong>($28, available at <a href=\"https://www.therunnerbox.com/product/riderbox/?ctc=brbgoutdoorbikinggeneralgg\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Runnerbox</a>) subscription goodie box ships every other month and is packed full of snacks, treats, and other fun stuff that makes every ride a little more tasty or interesting. They start at about $24/month with an annual subscription, but usually have almost $50 worth of stuff in there, plus discount codes for the things you want more of!</p><p>The <strong>Uncharted Supply Co. Triage Kit</strong> ($40, available at <a href=\"https://www.avantlink.com/click.php?tt=el&amp;merchant_id=b5770911-39dc-46ac-ba0f-b49dbb30c5c7&amp;website_id=3407ca35-0b50-44fe-aeb1-9ab6a93bba54&amp;url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.backcountry.com%2Funcharted-supply-co.-triage-kit&amp;ctc=brbgoutdoorbikinggeneralgg|xid:fr1635716343820gfe\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\" data-orig-url=\"https://www.avantlink.com/click.php?tt=el&amp;merchant_id=b5770911-39dc-46ac-ba0f-b49dbb30c5c7&amp;website_id=3407ca35-0b50-44fe-aeb1-9ab6a93bba54&amp;url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.backcountry.com%2Funcharted-supply-co.-triage-kit&amp;ctc=brbgoutdoorbikinggeneralgg\" data-ml-id=\"8\" data-ml=\"true\" data-xid=\"fr1635716343820gfe\">Backcountry</a> and <a href=\"https://www.amazon.com/dp/B08FBP6WQY/?tag=20br-20\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\" data-orig-url=\"https://www.amazon.com/dp/B08FBP6WQY/?tag=20br-20\" data-ml-id=\"9\" data-ml=\"true\" data-xid=\"fr1635716343820eab\">Amazon</a>) is a compact first aid kit in a waterproof pouch that fits in a jersey pocket. Which means it’ll fit in a hip pack, hydration pack, or your glove box just fine, too. We take one with us on almost every ride, and there’s a bit extra room to customize it with whatever meds or little additions you want to add.</p><h2>Best Cycling Gifts under $100</h2><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/25183516/HGG-general-100.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/25183516/HGG-general-100.jpg\" alt=\"best gifts for cyclists under 100 dollars\" width=\"1539\" height=\"989\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/25183516/HGG-general-100.jpg 1539w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/25183516/HGG-general-100-297x191.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/25183516/HGG-general-100-800x514.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/25183516/HGG-general-100-120x77.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/25183516/HGG-general-100-768x494.jpg 768w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/25183516/HGG-general-100-1536x987.jpg 1536w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1539px) 100vw, 1539px\"></a></p><p>The <strong>Muc-Off 8 in 1 Bicycle Cleaning Kit</strong> ($70, available at <a href=\"https://www.avantlink.com/click.php?tt=el&amp;merchant_id=e295c418-295a-447c-b265-734e25f82503&amp;website_id=3407ca35-0b50-44fe-aeb1-9ab6a93bba54&amp;url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.rei.com%2Fproduct%2F131914%2Fmuc-off-8-in-1-bicycle-cleaning-kit&amp;ctc=brbgoutdoorbikinggeneralgg|xid:fr1635716343820jgj\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\" data-orig-url=\"https://www.avantlink.com/click.php?tt=el&amp;merchant_id=e295c418-295a-447c-b265-734e25f82503&amp;website_id=3407ca35-0b50-44fe-aeb1-9ab6a93bba54&amp;url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.rei.com%2Fproduct%2F131914%2Fmuc-off-8-in-1-bicycle-cleaning-kit&amp;ctc=brbgoutdoorbikinggeneralgg\" data-ml-id=\"10\" data-ml=\"true\" data-xid=\"fr1635716343820jgj\">REI</a> and <a href=\"https://www.avantlink.com/click.php?tt=el&amp;merchant_id=92594cfb-2b30-40ba-ab76-f9c20ed4612c&amp;website_id=3407ca35-0b50-44fe-aeb1-9ab6a93bba54&amp;url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.competitivecyclist.com%2Fmuc-off-8-in-1-bicycle-cleaning-kit&amp;ctc=brbgoutdoorbikinggeneralgg|xid:fr1635716343820ffc\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\" data-orig-url=\"https://www.avantlink.com/click.php?tt=el&amp;merchant_id=92594cfb-2b30-40ba-ab76-f9c20ed4612c&amp;website_id=3407ca35-0b50-44fe-aeb1-9ab6a93bba54&amp;url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.competitivecyclist.com%2Fmuc-off-8-in-1-bicycle-cleaning-kit&amp;ctc=brbgoutdoorbikinggeneralgg\" data-ml-id=\"11\" data-ml=\"true\" data-xid=\"fr1635716343820ffc\">Competitive Cyclist</a>) gets you all of the essential brushes to clean every part of your bike, plus a spray-on cleaner that gently releases grime from your chain or road spray. We like this because it lets us add whatever degreaser and chain lube we like, and it’s half the price of their bigger kit while still giving you all the right brushes.</p><p>Regardless of what type of cyclist you’re buying for, there are times when we’ll skip the full Spandex kit but we still want <em>some</em> padding. Whether it’s for a long spin around town, or casual ride with friends. The <strong>Club Ride Woodchuck</strong> (Men’s, $55 available at <a href=\"https://www.amazon.com/dp/B07PYYK8CT/?tag=20br-20\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\" data-orig-url=\"https://www.amazon.com/dp/B07PYYK8CT/?tag=20br-20\" data-ml-id=\"12\" data-ml=\"true\" data-xid=\"fr1635716343820hce\">Amazon</a> and <a href=\"https://www.avantlink.com/click.php?tt=el&amp;merchant_id=e8731266-6976-491c-a059-81fd23a1c789&amp;website_id=3407ca35-0b50-44fe-aeb1-9ab6a93bba54&amp;url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.clubrideapparel.com%2Fcollections%2Fmens-bike-shorts-chamois%2Fproducts%2Fwoodchuck-mens-bike-short&amp;ctc=brbgoutdoorbikinggeneralgg|xid:fr1635716343820jia\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\" data-orig-url=\"https://www.avantlink.com/click.php?tt=el&amp;merchant_id=e8731266-6976-491c-a059-81fd23a1c789&amp;website_id=3407ca35-0b50-44fe-aeb1-9ab6a93bba54&amp;url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.clubrideapparel.com%2Fcollections%2Fmens-bike-shorts-chamois%2Fproducts%2Fwoodchuck-mens-bike-short&amp;ctc=brbgoutdoorbikinggeneralgg\" data-ml-id=\"13\" data-ml=\"true\" data-xid=\"fr1635716343820jia\">Club Ride Apparel</a>) and <strong>Montcham</strong> (Women’s, $55 available at <a href=\"https://amazon.com/dp/B07H9X9DD3/?tag=20br-20\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\" data-orig-url=\"https://amazon.com/dp/B07H9X9DD3/?tag=20br-20\" data-ml-id=\"14\" data-ml=\"true\" data-xid=\"fr1635716343820dbc\">Amazon</a> and <a href=\"https://www.avantlink.com/click.php?tt=el&amp;merchant_id=e8731266-6976-491c-a059-81fd23a1c789&amp;website_id=3407ca35-0b50-44fe-aeb1-9ab6a93bba54&amp;url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.clubrideapparel.com%2Fcollections%2Fwomen-bike-shorts-chamois%2Fproducts%2Fmontcham-womens-bike-short&amp;ctc=brbgoutdoorbikinggeneralgg|xid:fr1635716343820ibj\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\" data-orig-url=\"https://www.avantlink.com/click.php?tt=el&amp;merchant_id=e8731266-6976-491c-a059-81fd23a1c789&amp;website_id=3407ca35-0b50-44fe-aeb1-9ab6a93bba54&amp;url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.clubrideapparel.com%2Fcollections%2Fwomen-bike-shorts-chamois%2Fproducts%2Fmontcham-womens-bike-short&amp;ctc=brbgoutdoorbikinggeneralgg\" data-ml-id=\"15\" data-ml=\"true\" data-xid=\"fr1635716343820ibj\">Club Ride Apparel</a>) are super comfortable under regular shorts (or even jeans), with just enough compression to support muscles on longer, harder rides, too. They’re great under MTB baggies, too!</p><p>Don’t forget your <strong>Local Bike Shop!</strong> In fact, any of this stuff you can find local should be bought locally. And let’s face it, there’s always going to be some repair we don’t wanna do ourselves or some part we need in a pinch. Buying local and supporting your favorite bike shop means they’ll be around when you need them! <strong>Grab a Gift Certificate</strong> to your cyclist’s favorite shop so they can get exactly what they need when they need it!</p><h2>Best Cycling Gifts under $250</h2><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/25181825/HGG-general-249.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/25181825/HGG-general-249.jpg\" alt=\"best cycling gifts under 250 dollars\" width=\"1400\" height=\"1068\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/25181825/HGG-general-249.jpg 1400w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/25181825/HGG-general-249-297x227.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/25181825/HGG-general-249-800x610.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/25181825/HGG-general-249-120x92.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/25181825/HGG-general-249-768x586.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1400px) 100vw, 1400px\"></a></p><p>Sure, you could get them good bike lights for far less money. But these <strong>Bontrager Ion 200 RT/Flare RT lights </strong>($120, available at <a href=\"https://www.avantlink.com/click.php?tt=el&amp;merchant_id=e295c418-295a-447c-b265-734e25f82503&amp;website_id=3407ca35-0b50-44fe-aeb1-9ab6a93bba54&amp;url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.rei.com%2Fproduct%2F152981%2Fbontrager-ion-200-rtflare-rt-light-set&amp;ctc=brbgoutdoorbikinggeneralgg|xid:fr1635716343820agb\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\" data-orig-url=\"https://www.avantlink.com/click.php?tt=el&amp;merchant_id=e295c418-295a-447c-b265-734e25f82503&amp;website_id=3407ca35-0b50-44fe-aeb1-9ab6a93bba54&amp;url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.rei.com%2Fproduct%2F152981%2Fbontrager-ion-200-rtflare-rt-light-set&amp;ctc=brbgoutdoorbikinggeneralgg\" data-ml-id=\"16\" data-ml=\"true\" data-xid=\"fr1635716343820agb\">REI</a> and <a href=\"https://www.avantlink.com/click.php?tt=el&amp;merchant_id=0d15472d-796a-41f7-afb4-32437118891b&amp;website_id=3407ca35-0b50-44fe-aeb1-9ab6a93bba54&amp;url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.trekbikes.com%2Fus%2Fen_US%2Fequipment%2Fbike-accessories%2Fbike-lights%2Fbike-light-sets%2Fbontrager-ion-200-rt%2Fflare-rt-light-set%2Fp%2F23710%2F&amp;ctc=brbgoutdoorbikinggeneralgg|xid:fr1635716343820bha\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\" data-orig-url=\"https://www.avantlink.com/click.php?tt=el&amp;merchant_id=0d15472d-796a-41f7-afb4-32437118891b&amp;website_id=3407ca35-0b50-44fe-aeb1-9ab6a93bba54&amp;url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.trekbikes.com%2Fus%2Fen_US%2Fequipment%2Fbike-accessories%2Fbike-lights%2Fbike-light-sets%2Fbontrager-ion-200-rt%2Fflare-rt-light-set%2Fp%2F23710%2F&amp;ctc=brbgoutdoorbikinggeneralgg\" data-ml-id=\"17\" data-ml=\"true\" data-xid=\"fr1635716343820bha\">Trek Bikes</a>) are some of the best we’ve tried. They’re tiny, ultra-lightweight, but are extremely bright and long-lasting. Their blink patterns can be seen from up to 2km away in full daylight, and they’re even bright enough to navigate dark backroads in a pinch, too.</p><p>Similarly, you can get cheaper floor pumps, but few if any will outlast a Silca. In fact, chances are this will get passed down to the next generation of cyclists from its original owner. &nbsp;The <strong>Silca Pista Plus Floor Pump </strong>($165, available at <a href=\"https://www.avantlink.com/click.php?tt=el&amp;merchant_id=e295c418-295a-447c-b265-734e25f82503&amp;website_id=3407ca35-0b50-44fe-aeb1-9ab6a93bba54&amp;url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.rei.com%2Fproduct%2F167782%2Fsilca-pista-plus-floor-pump&amp;ctc=brbgoutdoorbikinggeneralgg|xid:fr1635716343820bfd\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\" data-orig-url=\"https://www.avantlink.com/click.php?tt=el&amp;merchant_id=e295c418-295a-447c-b265-734e25f82503&amp;website_id=3407ca35-0b50-44fe-aeb1-9ab6a93bba54&amp;url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.rei.com%2Fproduct%2F167782%2Fsilca-pista-plus-floor-pump&amp;ctc=brbgoutdoorbikinggeneralgg\" data-ml-id=\"18\" data-ml=\"true\" data-xid=\"fr1635716343820bfd\">REI</a>) is a do-it-all pump with their special Presta valve chuck that makes it quick and easy to inflate any bike you’ve got. And it’s fully rebuildable, so it won’t end up in the landfill if something does break.</p><p>The <strong>Chrome Urban EX 2.0 Rolltop 30L Backpack </strong>($145, available at <a href=\"https://www.avantlink.com/click.php?tt=el&amp;merchant_id=e295c418-295a-447c-b265-734e25f82503&amp;website_id=3407ca35-0b50-44fe-aeb1-9ab6a93bba54&amp;url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.rei.com%2Fproduct%2F180106%2Fchrome-urban-ex-20-rolltop-30l-pack&amp;ctc=brbgoutdoorbikinggeneralgg|xid:fr1635716343820jdj\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\" data-orig-url=\"https://www.avantlink.com/click.php?tt=el&amp;merchant_id=e295c418-295a-447c-b265-734e25f82503&amp;website_id=3407ca35-0b50-44fe-aeb1-9ab6a93bba54&amp;url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.rei.com%2Fproduct%2F180106%2Fchrome-urban-ex-20-rolltop-30l-pack&amp;ctc=brbgoutdoorbikinggeneralgg\" data-ml-id=\"19\" data-ml=\"true\" data-xid=\"fr1635716343820jdj\">REI</a> and <a href=\"https://www.avantlink.com/click.php?tt=el&amp;merchant_id=e295c418-295a-447c-b265-734e25f82503&amp;website_id=3407ca35-0b50-44fe-aeb1-9ab6a93bba54&amp;url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.rei.com%2Fproduct%2F180106%2Fchrome-urban-ex-20-rolltop-30l-pack&amp;ctc=brbgoutdoorbikinggeneralgg|xid:fr1635716343820jhh\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\" data-orig-url=\"https://www.avantlink.com/click.php?tt=el&amp;merchant_id=e295c418-295a-447c-b265-734e25f82503&amp;website_id=3407ca35-0b50-44fe-aeb1-9ab6a93bba54&amp;url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.rei.com%2Fproduct%2F180106%2Fchrome-urban-ex-20-rolltop-30l-pack&amp;ctc=brbgoutdoorbikinggeneralgg\" data-ml-id=\"20\" data-ml=\"true\" data-xid=\"fr1635716343820jhh\">Competitive Cyclist</a>) may not look like much or have any bells and whistles, but that’s exactly what makes it so useful. Headed to the grocery store? You can shove a ton of food in this. Or a case of beer with ice (it’s 100% waterproof). Or a bunch of clothes for changing at work <em>and</em> the gym. It’s a giant, gaping black hole of a bag that works for anything without tiny pockets and organizers dictating how you use it (though it does have a padded laptop sleeve). If you don’t have a cargo bike, you need a bag like this.</p><h2>Best Cycling Gifts over $250</h2><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/25184425/HGG-general-250.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/25184425/HGG-general-250.jpg\" alt=\"best holiday gifts for cyclists over 250 dollars\" width=\"1416\" height=\"907\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/25184425/HGG-general-250.jpg 1416w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/25184425/HGG-general-250-297x190.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/25184425/HGG-general-250-800x512.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/25184425/HGG-general-250-120x77.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/25184425/HGG-general-250-768x492.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1416px) 100vw, 1416px\"></a></p><p>If your favorite cyclist gets out early to ride, consider this one a gift to yourself, too. The <strong>Fellows Ode Brew Grinder</strong> ($299, available at <a href=\"https://www.amazon.com/dp/B08V3VFXCN/?tag=20br-20\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\" data-orig-url=\"https://www.amazon.com/dp/B08V3VFXCN/?tag=20br-20\" data-ml-id=\"21\" data-ml=\"true\" data-xid=\"fr1635716343820cfb\">Amazon</a>) is a remarkably quiet burr grinder that delivers excellent results. Which means they get the caffeinated lifeblood that nearly every rider lives for, and you get to stay soundly asleep. Seriously, we can’t believe how quiet this coffee grinder is!</p><p>Every cyclist should have a good workstand, and our favorite is the <strong>Feedback Sports Pro-Elite Bike Repair Stand</strong> ($330, available at <a href=\"https://www.feedbacksports.com/product/pro-elite-repair-stand/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">REI</a> and <a href=\"https://www.avantlink.com/click.php?tt=el&amp;merchant_id=b5770911-39dc-46ac-ba0f-b49dbb30c5c7&amp;website_id=3407ca35-0b50-44fe-aeb1-9ab6a93bba54&amp;url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.backcountry.com%2Ffeedback-sports-pro-elite-bicycle-repair-stand&amp;ctc=brbgoutdoorbikinggeneralgg|xid:fr1635716343820dhb\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\" data-orig-url=\"https://www.avantlink.com/click.php?tt=el&amp;merchant_id=b5770911-39dc-46ac-ba0f-b49dbb30c5c7&amp;website_id=3407ca35-0b50-44fe-aeb1-9ab6a93bba54&amp;url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.backcountry.com%2Ffeedback-sports-pro-elite-bicycle-repair-stand&amp;ctc=brbgoutdoorbikinggeneralgg\" data-ml-id=\"22\" data-ml=\"true\" data-xid=\"fr1635716343820dhb\">Backcountry</a>). Their entry- and mid-level stands are great, too, but this top-of-the-line model’s quick release clamp is what sets it apart. Top-notch construction, an ultrawide base for supporting heavy bikes (even e-mountain bikes), and a lightweight design that folds down very compact for storage combine to make it a workstand that’ll last for many, many years.</p><p>If we’re dreaming big, then we think everyone should have an e-Cargo Bike. They make short trips around town a breeze, whether it’s a grocery run, taking kids to school, hitting the farmer’s market, or even taking your sweetie out on a date, the <strong>Yuba Spicy Curry</strong> ($4,900, available at <a href=\"https://www.avantlink.com/click.php?tt=el&amp;merchant_id=e295c418-295a-447c-b265-734e25f82503&amp;website_id=3407ca35-0b50-44fe-aeb1-9ab6a93bba54&amp;url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.rei.com%2Fproduct%2F170547%2Fyuba-spicy-curry-v3-electric-bike&amp;ctc=brbgoutdoorbikinggeneralgg|xid:fr1635716343820dcf\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\" data-orig-url=\"https://www.avantlink.com/click.php?tt=el&amp;merchant_id=e295c418-295a-447c-b265-734e25f82503&amp;website_id=3407ca35-0b50-44fe-aeb1-9ab6a93bba54&amp;url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.rei.com%2Fproduct%2F170547%2Fyuba-spicy-curry-v3-electric-bike&amp;ctc=brbgoutdoorbikinggeneralgg\" data-ml-id=\"23\" data-ml=\"true\" data-xid=\"fr1635716343820dcf\">REI</a>) is one of our faves. We’ve been riding one for years, and it is quite literally a life-changing bike. You’ll be surprised at how often you ditch the car in favor of riding this!</p><hr><p><em>Disclosure: The Rider Box is a sponsored inclusion in this list, but we love them (and have a few subscriptions to it ourselves!). We will only ever recommend products that we actually like, and every item in our Gift Guides has been tested or used by one of more of our team members.</em></p></section></article></div></div>","author":"Tyler Benedict","siteTitle":"Bikerumor","siteHash":"49f427af0a926f4232eb837006841d7242e153e3afbb590f32e4b104ea3e2718","entryHash":"b793fd892e1d0c742ff9a3e0af4a8bc5acce0078ca99c1dc3295be2dc9d2b731","category":"Cycling"}